	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />We all know that when a game is inserted into an NES and is pushed down, it bends the pins gradually ruining the 72-pin connector. Does anyone know a way to fix this?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


