		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have the SNES kit. It is like a weird foam board thing in the shape of the connector. I think it also came with some kind of wet and dry brush and some kind of liquid solution you put on it. So you used the wet side of the brush and solution on your cartridges. Then the dry side. For the console you just put the cleaning cartridge with the weird white foam thing inside it and repeatedly insert and remove the cartridge to remove nasty stuff. It worked well.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


